After  you  have unpacked your kit, you should have some files
listed in README.

     README                      this files
     epicon.h                    header file
     epicon.c                    epicon command interface
     epicon_main.c               epicon main process
     epicon_uty.c                epicon utility
     sample.scr                  sample batch script
     patch-gkermit1.0+counter1.2.1 patch for indicating a counter
     configure                   create of Makefile script
     Makefile.am                 source of Makefile.in
     Makefile.in                 source of Makefile
     etc..

Installation
1) Detailed instructions are in the file after
   INSTALL which you should read.In brief, the following should
   work on most systems:
   ncurses-devel.i386 is necessary for make. 
   * ncurses-devel.i386 : Development files for the ncurses library
      ./configure
      make
      make install       

2)epicon  UNINSTALL
      make  uninstall        

3)epicon object CLEAN
      make clean
 
4)Read the manual entries before running epicon.
      man epicon

5)before running epicon
  If a thing to prepare for is said, the rest is the skill which
  can cook router connected to the cable.

6)after running epicon
  This software may still keep containing many bugs by the 
  un-maturity.
  There probably are some, but I don't know what they are yet.
  It  is lucky if I can have a report and advice by mail if a bug
  is found.
  If possible, send in patches such that the patch  program  will
  apply them.
  Context diffs are the best, then normal diffs.
  The  thing that the version of epicon which if you have is won-
  derful changes mine.

7)Known bug
  Any file transfers other than automatic reception of ZMODEM
  binary mode not supported.(TCP/IP)

